r> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/31/02 7:11:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1642.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Some questions.</span><hr size=1> Hi, I have a few questions on gameplay.<br>
<br>
1) Do channels override language problems?<br>
<br>
2) Please explain grouping and class/race restrictions. For example, is there anyway a Cat shaman could group with a Dark Elf Necro?<br>
<br>
3) How do you find a pickup group? Also see my thread on #lfg.<br>
<br>
4) What forms of communication are left? /say, /send, /gu only - there are no zone wide channels at all?<br>
<br>
5) do the /who commands work?<br>
<br>
6) Finally, what are the funstoppers, in your opinions - what rules that are FV only really annoy you? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/31/02 7:26:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1642.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some questions.</span><hr size=1> 1)  Yes, but that should be fixed soon... I hope.<br>
<br>
2)  Evils cannot group with goods, unless a nuetral leads them.  Discords and Orders in the same group get an exp penalty.  A group of all one type (ie all order goods) gets an exp bonus.  Nuetrals never get this bonus.<br>
<br>
3)  We walk into a zone and send tells.  A polite query (Hi there, I'm a 40th season rogue... need company in battle) works just fine.<br>
<br>
4)  No zone channels in non city zones.  Say and groupsay, as well as guildchat, are the same as your other servers.  Shout has a range on it, about twice as long as say.  Auction is permitted in city zones only.  OOC is not permitted at all.<br>
<br>
5)  A who command will show everyone as annonymous.  So doing a /who in a zone will tell you the names of those in zone, their guilds, and wether they are AFK/LFG/LD<br>
<br>
6)  None, I love it.  It's a much better environment.  Sure, trivial loot can be a pain sometimes... but it adds to things as well in many ways... less farming is nice, and being paid with a Lodi belt for a goblin skull earing ain't bad either.<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/4/02 5:13:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1642.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some questions.</span><hr size=1> 1) Yes, but it's a bug and will be fixed someday.<br>
<br>
2) There's a bug which allows Evils and Goods to group together, but they still can't cast beneficial spells (e.g., buffs and heals) on each other.<br>
<br>
3) Just ask around.  It helps to join a guild if you find one that suits your playstyle.<br>
<br>
4) OOC is gone.  Shout has limited range.  Auction only in &quot;city&quot; zones.<br>
<br>
5) Everyone is anonymous.  Otherwise it's the same as any other server.<br>
<br>
6) Everyone is anonymous.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhalus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Halus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/4/02 8:17:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1642.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some questions.</span><hr size=1> 3. ... Go to spots you'd usually go to at your level. You'll almost always find people in highpass/highkeep, for example. Huge zones like Lake of Ill Omen are more difficult because you have to look harder to find people. <br>
People on this server know what it's like to be without a group and are very understanding. I've never been in a group with vacancies that didn't invite whoever asked till all the slots were filled up.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufeneant.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feneant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 462<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/4/02 12:16:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1642.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some questions.</span><hr size=1> 6) Finally, what are the funstoppers, in your opinions - what rules that are FV only really annoy you? <br>
