-Anonymouse kills pick up groups<br>
<br>
Why not ? Simple - you still can get groups. You just cant run into a huge zone, do a who, and pick out the ones you might want to group with. You actually have to walk up to them and talk. It is something which at least nudges people towards roleplay. It also means that (as someone before said), you most likely will be invited into a group if there is room, even if your class isnt *quite* what they would take on a &quot;normal&quot; blue server.<br>
<br>
-Expect to reroll often<br>
<br>
I havent rerolled.. not once. And i still am happy. Granted, FV is not the ideal server to try out that odd combo you never had. But if you think about what you want to play before creating a char, you should get a good chance of staying with that. <br>
On the other hand, the one char rule has limited twinking and other effects extremly common on other servers, so in my (very personal view), the one character per player rule is a big plus.<br>
<br>
Most of the other questions are covered already. So i'll limit myself to answering 6)<br>
a) the lack of an easy to learn language which is limited to basic sentences - basically the ability to communicate with others on a &quot;base&quot; level (Something like &quot;i hungry&quot; or &quot;you dead&quot;)<br>
b) The fact that you cant seem to protect &quot;your&quot; guards / npc friends. I'd love the ability to heal / buff npc's with amiable faction to me. It would give a whole new meaning to the sentence &quot;And the dark elves gathered to fend off the invasion of the Dwarves&quot;<br>
<br>
